Question 3

What is a degenerate dimension?

Answer:
A degenerate dimension is a dimension attribute that is stored directly in the fact table 
instead of creating a separate dimension table. 
It usually contains only an identifier and no additional descriptive attributes.

Example

Sales_Fact
-----------
order_id   ← Degenerate Dimension
product_id
customer_id
date_id
quantity
amount

In this example, order_id is a degenerate dimension because it is kept in the fact table
and does not have its own dimension table.

When to use:
 When the attribute is just an identifier
 When there are no descriptive columns
 When creating a separate dimension table is unnecessary
